                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On November 19, 1951, Secretary of State Acheson spoke before the First Committee
                    of the General Assembly in support and elaboration of the tripartite resolution
                    on regulation, limitation, and balanced reduction of all armed forces and all
                    armaments, document A/C.1/667 <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>. For the summary
                    record of his remarks, see United Nations, <hi rend="italic">Official Records of
                        the General Assembly, Sixth Session, First Committee</hi>, pages 7–10
                    (hereafter cited as <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> (VI), <hi rend="italic"
                        >First Committee</hi>). For the full text of the address, Department of
                    State press release 1040, November 20, 1951, see <hi rend="italic">Documents on
                        Disarmament, 1945–1959</hi>, volume I, pages 309–330.</p>
            </div>
